project: Priceplain
goal: Help founders price AI apps without hand-building monetisation logic.

primary_user:
  role: Founder of a newly built AI app
  context: Has rough usage costs, uncertain willingness to pay, and limited time before launch
  job_to_be_done: Produce a credible first pricing model with usage limits, margin visibility, and billing assumptions

challenge_focus:
  primary:
    - Solvimon: strongest chance of becoming a real business
    - Codeplain: best project built with spec-driven development
  secondary:
    - Vercel: deployable app using the Vercel AI SDK for Claude refinement
    - FLock: sovereign AI governance review with optional FLock-compatible inference
  out_of_scope:
    - Sui: requires a real on-chain app using Sui technology
    - Bilt: requires a working mobile app on bilt.me and go-to-market signal
    - BGA: requires trading, portfolio, or market-strategy tooling

core_flow:
  - Founder enters product description, audience, value metric, active users, costs, fixed costs, margin target, conversion, churn, and growth
  - System calculates cost per active customer and marginal unit economics
  - System generates Free, Starter, Growth, and Scale pricing tiers
  - System proposes metering events for billing and analytics
  - System creates a Solvimon Handoff pipeline with value metric, meter events, plans, invoice_items, credit_policies, JSON export, a compact developer billing object, implementation notes, and JSON handoff data
  - System simulates revenue, cost of goods sold, gross margin, and break-even over twelve months
  - System stress-tests pricing with model-cost shock, usage spike, conversion drop, and churn rise scenarios
  - System compares saved AI-app presets so judges can see the model works across different business shapes
  - System presents a business case that maps to Solvimon and Codeplain judging criteria
  - System shows whether Claude and FLock keys are configured without exposing secrets
  - Claude reviews the generated model for pricing rationale, Solvimon fit, and Codeplain implementation next steps when an API key is configured
  - Vercel AI SDK provides the structured server-side AI generation path
  - System provides a Sovereign AI Review for institutional buyers evaluating governance, data ownership, auditability, procurement risk, and FLock-compatible inference paths
  - System exports landing-page pricing copy, sensitivity checks, and a Solvimon-style billing handoff as Markdown
  - System provides a final Submission Pack view with a Solvimon Judge Lens, winning summary, track coverage, demo script, and submission checklist
  - Demo mode hides the intake form and focuses the visible tabs on Pricing, Solvimon Handoff, Revenue Simulation, Startup Case, and Submission Pack
  - Documentation includes an optional Solvimon checkout guide for creating a hosted test checkout page from the Priceplain handoff using Solvimon MCP

non_goals_for_mvp:
  - No payment collection
  - No production billing integration
  - No customer accounts
  - No live quote-to-cash automation
  - No broad sponsor-track coverage outside Solvimon, Codeplain, Vercel, and FLock

success_criteria:
  - A judge can understand the startup use case in under one minute
  - The generated tiers are tied to usage costs rather than arbitrary price guesses
  - The pricing output includes explicit metering assumptions
  - The Solvimon Handoff includes a readable pipeline, meters, plans, invoice_items, credit_policies, implementation notes, compact developer object, and JSON handoff data
  - The Solvimon import preview can be copied or downloaded as JSON
  - The simulation makes margin and free-tier risk visible
  - Sensitivity checks show how fragile the model is under cost, usage, conversion, and churn changes
  - The Submission Pack tab compares the saved presets
  - The Submission Pack tab explains demand, monetisation, differentiation, post-hackathon plan, and demo tone using the Solvimon Judge Lens
  - The Submission Pack tab explains why Priceplain stands out
  - The Startup Case tab explains customer, problem, wedge, revenue path, Solvimon fit, and Codeplain fit
  - The sovereign review tab explains data sovereignty, auditability, vendor lock-in, public-sector suitability, procurement questions, governance actions, and FLock path
  - The Submission Pack tab contains a judge-ready demo script and submission checklist
  - The Solvimon checkout guide explains sandbox creation, API key creation, MCP setup, checkout link generation and test-card checkout
  - The report can be downloaded as Markdown
  - The demo works without external credentials
  - Provider status clearly distinguishes configured and missing live keys
  - Claude enhancement degrades gracefully when credentials are missing
